description:
&lt;p&gt;Mid and South Essex NHS Foundation Trust was established on 1st April 2020 following the merger between Basildon &amp; Thurrock Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust, Mid Essex Hospital NHS Trust and Southend University Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust. The Trust is undertaking an ambitious programme of work to migrate all clinical and corporate IT applications in use across the organisation onto supported technical platforms.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an experienced Change Analyst within the Digital Services Department. Reporting to the Test Team Manager the Change Analyst will be required to communicate and deliver changes within the processes to support the migration of clinical and corporate business applications onto supported technical platforms.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a key part of a dynamic and evolving service, Change Analyst will have a strong client focus, manage complex and sensitive information, liaise and communicate with clinical and non-clinical staff as necessary to ensure all requests are delivered within our published Trust information security policies. The ability to work with operational teams to undertake full business analysis is required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
